      • initialize

        public static void initialize​(Scroll.ScrollFactor scrollFactor)
        Set the default scrollFactor for all subsequent calls to Scroll functions. Default is ScrollFactor.MEDIUM.
        Parameters:
        scrollFactor - new default value for scrollFactor when performing scrolling.

      • scrollListToElementWithText

        public static boolean scrollListToElementWithText​(java.lang.String elementText,
                                                  java.lang.Integer timeout)
        Scrolls through a list of all text elements on the screen, attempting to find the requested text. Throws an exception if the text is not found. Android only.

        For iOS, it is preferred to use scrollListToElementWithText(String elementId, String elementText, Integer timeout)

        WARNING: In Android, buttons are also TextViews, so if a resource-id is not specified, then a footer button might be considered part of the scroll list, which could prevent scrolling of the actual list elements. It is always best practice to include a resource-id if possible.

        Parameters:
        elementText - text to attempt to find in the scrolling list.
        timeout - delay in seconds between each scroll action.
        Returns:
        true if the text was found.

      • scrollListToElementWithText

        public static boolean scrollListToElementWithText​(java.lang.String elementText,
                                                  Scroll.ScrollFactor scrollFactor,
                                                  java.lang.Integer timeout)
        Scrolls through a list of all text elements on the screen, attempting to find the requested text. Throws an exception if the text is not found. Android only.

        For iOS, it is preferred to use scrollListToElementWithText(String elementId, String elementText, Integer timeout)

        WARNING: In Android, buttons are also TextViews, so if a resource-id is not specified, then a footer button might be considered part of the scroll list, which could prevent scrolling of the actual list elements. It is always best practice to include a resource-id if possible.

        Parameters:
        elementText - text to attempt to find in the scrolling list.
        scrollFactor - how big the scroll action should be before releasing, from SMALL to XLARGE
        timeout - delay in seconds between each scroll action.
        Returns:
        true if the text was found.

      • scrollListToElementWithText

        public static boolean scrollListToElementWithText​(java.lang.String elementId,
                                                  java.lang.String elementText,
                                                  java.lang.Integer timeout)
        Scrolls through a list of a specific collection of elements on the screen, attempting to find the requested text. Throws an exception if the text is not found.
        Parameters:
        elementId - identifier of the collection of text elements to scroll (Accessibility id/name for iOS and resource-id for Android).
        elementText - text to attempt to find in the scrolling list.
        timeout - delay in seconds between each scroll action.
        Returns:
        true if the text was found.

      • scrollListToCheckboxWithText

        public static boolean scrollListToCheckboxWithText​(java.lang.String elementText,
                                                   java.lang.Integer timeout)
        Scrolls through a list of all checkbox elements on the screen, attempting to find the requested text. Throws an exception if the text is not found.

        For iOS, it is preferred to use scrollListToElementWithText(String elementId, String elementText, Integer timeout) so that an elementId can be specified, narrowing the search.

        Parameters:
        elementText - text to attempt to find in the scrolling list.
        timeout - delay in seconds between each scroll action.
        Returns:
        true if the text was found.
